This is our collection of links to Hualapai legends and traditional stories that can be read online.
We have indexed our <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/legends.htm">American Indian legends</a> section
by tribe to make them easier to locate<B>;</B> however, variants on the same
legend are often told by American Indians from different tribes, especially if those tribes are kinfolk or neighbors to
each other. In particular, though these legends come from the Hualapai, the mythology of
related tribes like the 
<a href="http://www.native-languages.org/mojave_culture.htm">Mojave</a> and 
<a href="http://www.native-languages.org/quechan.htm">Yuma</a> are very similar.
<BR><BR>
Enjoy the stories! If you would like to recommend a Hualapai story for this page or think one of the ones on here 
should be removed, please let us know.

<BR><BR>

