<H2><U>
<a name="figures">Hualapai Mythological Figures</a>
</u></H2>

<B><img src="vinesmall.jpg"><font size=4><I><U>Tochopa</font></U></B></I> (also spelled To-Cho-Pa, Tochopo, or Tudjupa):
The great Creator god of the Hualapai.
<br><br>
<B><img src="vinesmall.jpg"><font size=4><I><U>Hokomata</font></U></B></I> (also spelled Ho-Ko-Ma-Ta):
Tochopa's twin brother, a god of discord who taught the people to make war.

<H2><U>
<a name="tribes">Hualapai Indian Folklore</a>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20120417130148/http://grand-canyon-vacation-information.com/hualapai-indian-legend.html
">How The Grand Canyon Was Formed</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Hualapai legend about the flooding of the earth and the creation of the Grand Canyon.
<BR>


